113 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
113 g Baby Tomatoes
56 g Carrot, julienned
56 g Salad Topping Mix
1 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
1 unit(s) Honey
¼ tsp Salt and Pepper*
2 tbsp Oil*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.   Halve tomatoes. Cut cucumber into 1/4-inch rounds.

Whisk together vinegar, honey and 2 tbsp oil in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper.

Add spring mix, carrots, tomatoes and cucumbers to the bowl with the dressing. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.

Divide salad between bowls. Sprinkle salad topper mix over top.